FFFFF>(12/15/01 1:05:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin And Paladins</span><hr size=1> The thing for me is this. Sure, maybe a small proportion of all players are in &quot;uber guilds,&quot; taking on the really tough mobs, but without these mobs to take on, what is the point in continually advancing your character? I'm not doing the alt. exp thing and getting Ntov gear for nothing, I'm doing it to be a more effective player. But I sure as hell don't need fancy equip and special skills to be an effective player in 1-2 group encounters. It's just overkill. Even when I wasn't lvl 60 and in an uber guild, half the reason I kept playing the game was in anticipation of the day when I would be able to go to the hardest zones and kill the hardest mobs. I remember seeing my first truly uber paladin, and the awe that I felt, and how much I wanted to be like that guy one day. <br>
<br>
I also think VI realizes that they're starting to deal with a top heavy population, and they have to give the 60s who aren't in big guilds something to do. So they create alt advancement, they put these exciting zones in that you can go to with a few friends and rack up the loot, and they put in a new race and class to twink, but in the end, I still think it's a temporary fix. In my mind, the high end stuff is a driving force in this game. If you look at this board, you have all these posts from pre-55 people asking about what their role is in the high end game, what skill is useful on raids, debating whether to get their epic or hold out for Ntov loot. While VI has a good ploy here, I seriously doubt they are neglecting their high end game, or their high end players. <br>
<br>
Trabious Strangeluv<br>
Crusader of Lotus Cult<br>
Quellious <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaauan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aauan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/15/01 7:11:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin And Paladins</span><hr size=1> high-end people are gonna get bored and filter out no matter what. but think about this way, on e-marr you got 1 guild who has cleared Ntov, 1 guild who has cleared VP and one guild who awakened the sleeper, they have done EVERYTHING in the game pre-luclin, except for tunare. thats 1 guild, e-marr is an old server with alot of high end uber guilds/players. pick-up raids are killing poh, PoG, PoF, PoA, VS and tons of other raid only places.<br>
<br>
so for all these other guilds, there is still tons of encounters for them to strive for. just because there is a new expansion, doesn't mean the old encounters are no longer in the game, the new uber guilds can still go back and clear ToV, the new uber guilds can go start killing dain still. <br>
<br>
i think they really screwed up in luclin, alienated alot of people who aren't in uber guilds. luclin seems fun as hell to me. to me, the &quot;big&quot; encounters i have fought, i've never got a single piece of loot, for me the thrill of the encounter is the kill, not the loot. i don't care if i can get a nice belt in maidens eye, easier than clearing Ntov, i would still LOVE to clear Ntov. hell, i'd like to just zone-in and SEE tov, let alone kill anything.<br>
<br>
